Crystal Meth

Health-Medical Documentary hosted by Mike Secher, published by National Geographic broadcasted as part of NG Drugs Inc series in 2011 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Drugs Inc: Crystal Meth 
Some call methamphetamine the &quot;Devil's Drug.&quot; Often made in less than an hour from a common cold remedy, this powerful stimulant is sweeping across the U.S. and Asia. Follow a raid on a suspected meth lab, stake out a neighborhood pharmacy where addicts attempt to accumulate cold and flu pills, and meet a neuroscientist urgently searching for a cure for addiction. See the dangers of meth and the unexpected physical damages caused by the drug. Also a &quot;cook&quot; producing meth from his home, while neglecting 2 year-old son, is busted by the Drug Task Force Some people take meth because of the long-lasting high that it gives. Methamphetamine causes numerous neurotransmitters to be released in the brain, producing a sense of euphoria that may last as long as 12 hours, depending on how the drug was taken.

